ries.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ho |first1=Olivia |title=Five new Covid-19 clusters in Singapore, as 596 new cases brings country\u2019s total to 6,588 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/596-new-covid-19-infections-confirmed-in-spore-majority-work-permit-holders-in-dorms |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n*South Korea has reported 15 new cases, bringing the total to 10,661 cases. There have also been a total of 234 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Spain reports 410 new deaths, bringing the total to 20,453. Spain has reported a total of 195,944 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Taiwan has reported 22 new cases, bringing the total to 420. 21 of the newly infected cases had been [[Republic of China Navy]] sailors who had taken part in a goodwill mission to Palau. Taiwan has reported a total of six deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Ukraine reports 343 new cases and 8 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 5,449 and 141 respectively; a total of 347 patients have recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 5449 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1513158085513958 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=uk |date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The United Kingdom has reported 596 hospital deaths, bringing the death toll to 16,060.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*The United States reports 2,009 new cases, bringing the total to 735,336. The US has reported a total of 40,585 deaths, with almost half of them originating in New York state.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Zimbabwe has reported a total of three deaths and 25 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*According to figures released by [[Johns Hopkins University]], more than 2.3&nbsp;million people have been infected and over 164,000 people have died.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n\n===20 April===\n*Canada has reported a total of 1,611 deaths and 33,922 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\">{{cite news| last1=Mayberry |first1=Kate |last2=Stepansky |first2=Joseph |title=Protests flare in US, coronavirus toll tops 40,000: Live updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-deaths-exceed-40000-live-updates-200419233722851.html |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=20 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421051601/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-deaths-exceed-40000-live-updates-200419233722851.html|archive-date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*China has reported 12 new cases (eight of them imported) and 49 new asymptomatic cases but no deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Ecuador has reported a total of over 10,000 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*France has reported a total of 20,265 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Germany has reported 1,775 new cases, bringing the total to 141,672. Germany has reported 110 new deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Ghana has confirmed a total of 834 cases and nine deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Indonesia has reported 85 new cases, bringing the total number to 6,070. Indonesia has reported eight new deaths, bringing the death toll to 590. 747 people have recovered while 49,700 tests have been conducted.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Italy has reported that 108,237 were being treated at home or recovering in hospital, a drop by 20 from the total reported on Sunday.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Iran has reported 91 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 5,209. Iran has reported a total of 83,505 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 36 new cases, bringing the country's total number of cases to 5,425. Malaysian authorities have discharged 98 patients, brinigng the total number of recoveries to 3,295. Malaysia has reported no new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos |first1=Joseph, Jr. |title=Covid-19: 36 new cases, no deaths for first time in a month |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/20/covid-19-36-new-cases-no-deaths-for-first-time-in-a-month |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=20 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200420101750/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/20/covid-19-36-new-cases-no-deaths-for-first-time-in-a-month |archivedate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The Netherlands has reported 750 new cases, bringing the total to 33,405. Dutch health authorities have also reported 67 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,751.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand has reported 9 new cases (7 confirmed and 2 probable), bringing the total to 1,440 (1,105 confirmed and 335 probable). NZ health authorities have also recovered 62 new recoveries, bringing the total to 974. Fourteen people remain hospitalised.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=20 April 2020|access-date=20 April 2020|archive-date=20 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420024636/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref>\n*The Philippines has confirmed 19 new deaths, bringing the total to 428. The dead include former Senator and government minister [[Heherson Alvarez]]. The Philippines has also confirmed 200, bringing the total to 6,459. 41 patients have recovered, bringing the total to 613.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Russia has confirmed 4,268 new cases, bringing the total to 47,121. 44 new deaths reported.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Singapore has reported 1,426 new cases, bringing the total to 8,014.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Clement |last2=Iau |first2=Jean |title=1,369 of the 1,426 coronavirus cases confirmed in S\u2019pore are foreign workers living in dormitories |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1426-new-coronavirus-cases-in-spore-in-new-daily-high |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=20 April 2020 |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n*South Korea has reported 20 new cases (13 from overseas), bringing the total to 10,764.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Spain has confirmed a total of 200,210 cases and 20,852 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Switzerland has reported 204 new cases, bringing the total to 27,944. The country has also reported  a total of 1,142 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Thailand has reported 27 new cases, bringing the total to 2,792. Thailand has also reported 47 deaths and 1,999 recoveries.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Turkey has reported 4,674 cases, bringing the total to 90,980. Turkey has also reported 123 deaths, bringing the death toll to 2,140. 13,430 people have recovered while 39,703 people have been tested.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 20 April reports\" />\n*Ukraine reports 261 new cases and 10 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 5,710 and 151 respectively; 359 patients have recovered overall.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 5710 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1514025572093876 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=20 April 2020 |language=uk |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===21 April===\n*Canada has reported a total of 37,382 cases and 1,728 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*China has reported 11 new cases and 37 asymptomatic cases but no new deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\">{{cite news |last1=Mayberry |first1=Kate |last2=Siddiqui |first2=Usaid |last3=Pietromarchi |first3=Virginia|title=Confirmed coronavirus cases top 2.5m worldwide: Live updates|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-dead-world-exceeds-170000-live-updates-200421005048334.html |accessdate=21 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=21 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422071609/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-dead-world-exceeds-170000-live-updates-200421005048334.html |archive-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Indonesia reports 375 new cases, bringing the total to 7,135. Indonesian health authorities also report 26 new deaths, taking the death toll to 616.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Italy has reported 534 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 24,648. Italy has reported over 180,000 cases and almost 49,000 recovered people.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Lebanon has reported a total of 677 cases and 21 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 57 new cases, bringing the total to 5,482. 54 more patients have been discharged, bringing the number of recoveries to 3,349. Malaysia has recorded three more fatalities, bringing the death toll to 92.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos Jr |first1=Joseph |title=Covid-19: 57 new cases bringing total to 5,482, three new fatalities, death toll now at 92 |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/21/covid-19-57-new-cases-bringing-total-to-5482-three-new-fatalities-death-toll-now-at-92 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=21 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200421112842/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/21/covid-19-57-new-cases-bringing-total-to-5482-three-new-fatalities-death-toll-now-at-92 |archivedate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*In Morocco, 68 people, mainly staff, have tested positive for the coronavirus in the southern city of [[Ouarzazate]].<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*The Netherlands has reported 729 new cases, bringing the total to 34,134. Dutch health authorities have reported 165 deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,916.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand has reported 5 new cases (2 confirmed and 3 probable) were reported, bringing the total to 1,445 (1,107 confirmed and 338 probable). NZ authorities also reported 32 new recoveries were reported, bringing the total to 1,006. The country also reported a new death, bringing the death toll to 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=21 April 2020|access-date=21 April 2020|archive-date=21 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200421015622/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|first=Jamie|last=Ensor|title=Coronavirus: One death, five new cases of COVID-19 in New Zealand|work=Newshub|date=21 April 2020|accessdate=21 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421020106/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|archive-date=21 April 2020}}</ref> In addition, a New Zealand traveller in Peru died after missing a repatriation flight, however this is not included in Ministry of Health figures.<ref name=\"NZ Herald Peru death\">{{cite news |last1=Henry |first1=Dubby |title=Covid 19 coronavirus: Kiwi, 49, found dead in Peru with Covid-19, family says |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12326247 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |work=[[New Zealand Herald]] |date=21 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421002800/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12326247 |archivedate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Pakistan has confirmed 17 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 192. Pakistan also confirmed 705 new cases, bringing the total to 9,214.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*The Philippines reports 9 new deaths, bringing the total to 437. The Philippines have reported 140 new cases, bringing the total to 6,599.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Singapore has reported 1,111 new cases, bringing the total to 9,125.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iau |first1=Jean |last2=Yong |first2=Clement |title=1,050 of the 1,111 coronavirus cases confirmed in S'pore are foreign workers living in dormitories |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1111-new-coronavirus-cases-take-singapore-tally-past-9000-mark |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=21 April 2020 |date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Spain has reported 430 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 21,282. Spain has reported nearly 4,000 new cases, bringing the total number of infections to 204,178.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Turkey has reported 4,611 new cases, bringing the total to 95,591. Turkey reported 119 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 2,259.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*Ukraine reports 415 new cases and 10 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 6,125 and 161 respectively; a total of 367 patients have recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 6125 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1514905918672508 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=21 April 2020 |language=uk |date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===22 April===\n*New Zealand has reported 6 new cases, bringing the total to 1,451 (1,113 confirmed and 338 probable). In addition, there had been 30 new recoveries, bringing the total to 1,036. Authorities have also reported another death, bringing the death toll to 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=22 April 2020|access-date=22 April 2020|archive-date=22 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422012153/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Woman in her 80s dies of Covid-19, bringing New Zealand's death toll to 14 |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/woman-in-her-80s-dies-covid-19-bringing-new-zealands-death-toll-14|work=[[1 News]]|date=22 April 2020|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n<!--\n===23 April===\n===24 April===\n===25 April===\n===26 April===\n===27 April===\n===28 April===\n===29 April===\n===30 April===\n-->\n\n== Summary ==\n\n===Timeline===\n\nCountries and territories that confirmed their first cases during April 2020:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5em;\"  | Date\n! style=\"width:25em;\" | Country or territory\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 April\n| {{flagdeco|Malawi}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malawi|Malawi]]\